            "body": "<p>Don't forget to use <code>next()<\/code> after having used <code>nextInt()<\/code> to consume the rest of the unread characters.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>for (int i = 0; i &lt; h.length; i++) {\n    System.out.println(i);\n    h[i] = new Holiday(in.nextLine(), in.nextLine(), in.nextInt());\n    in.next();\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>Here is your entry<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>aaa bbb 1 ccc vvv\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>If you don't use <code>in.next()<\/code>, this is what will happen :<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>LOOP 1 :\n\nin.nextLine()    -&gt;    aaa\nin.nextLine()    -&gt;    bbb\nin.nextInt()     -&gt;    1\n\n//This looks OK.\n\nLOOP 2 :\n\nin.nextLine()    -&gt;    **UNREAD CHARACTER LEFT AFTER in.nextInt()**\nin.nextLine()    -&gt;    ccc\nin.nextInt()     -&gt;    vvv **INPUT MISMATCH BECAUSE IT IS NOT AN INT**\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 37772753,
            "question_id": 37772733,
            "last_edit_date": 1465724440
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/ACdqv.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 6979720,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 5353128,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5353128/kaushal28",
                "reputation": 5583,
                "display_name": "Kaushal28",
                "accept_rate": 73
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1465724368,
            "creation_date": 1465724368,
            "body": "<p>Just use <code>in.next()<\/code> instead of <code>in.nextLine()<\/code>.\nClick <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22458575/whats-the-difference-between-next-and-nextline-methods-from-scanner-class\">here<\/a> to see the difference.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 37772770,
            "question_id": 37772733,
            "last_edit_date": 1495540723
        }
    ],
